I've also checked that the nightly builds work fine.

[~marcbernot] Can you try to install a nightly build?
{code:java}
conda update -c arrow-nightlies pyarrow

{code}

[~apitrou] Even with the nightly wheel build, it crashes with the below.
{code}
Process finished with exit code -1073741795 (0xC000001D)
{code}
It does however work fine with the below conda env, which leads me to suspect the snappy patch is missing in the wheel build.
{code}
conda create -c conda-forge -n pyarrow_test python=3.8 pyarrow=2.0.0
{code}
